WEBVTT

00:00.200 --> 00:00.245
<Font color=#FFFFO0>Love Me Dead</font>

00:00.258 --> 00:01.237
There are two kinds of folks

00:01.264 --> 00:02.864
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:03.198 --> 00:04.924
psychopaths and mystery writers.

00:05.262 --> 00:06.284
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:06.585 --> 00:07.285
Who am I?

00:07.374 --> 00:08.513
I'm Rick Castle.

00:08.514 --> 00:09.608
Castle.

00:08.948 --> 00:09.608
Castle.

00:09.609 --> 00:11.609
I really am ruggedly handsome,
aren't I?

00:11.855 --> 00:14.045
Every writer needs inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:14.155 --> 00:14.974
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:15.009 --> 00:16.029
- Beckett.
- Beckett.

00:16.064 --> 00:17.970
- Nikki Heat?
- The character he's basing on you.

00:18.116 --> 00:19.702
And thanks to my friendship
with the mayor,

00:19.703 --> 00:20.703
I get to be on her case.

00:20.937 --> 00:22.880
I would be happy
to let you spank me.

00:22.915 --> 00:23.991
And together, we catch killers

00:24.739 --> 00:25.827
We make a pretty
good team, you know?

00:25.928 --> 00:26.928
Like Starsky and Hutch.

00:27.062 --> 00:27.956
Turner and Hooch.

00:28.057 --> 00:29.757
You do remind me
a little of Hooch.

00:31.253 --> 00:33.055
♪ oh-a-oh-oh ♪¶

00:33.256 --> 00:35.157
♪ oh-a-oh-oh ♪

00:35.558 --> 00:37.760
I have to laugh at her jokes.
She's my boss.

00:37.761 --> 00:39.263
Do you have to stare
at her boobs, too?

00:39.464 --> 00:40.764
I wasn't. She had a stain.

00:40.864 --> 00:42.832
And you were trying
to memorize the shape?

00:43.033 --> 00:45.001
What? No. I swear.

00:46.402 --> 00:48.737
If I'm lying,
my God strike me down...

00:49.040 --> 00:50.040
Oh! Aah!

00:50.640 --> 00:51.407
Oh!

00:55.411 --> 00:56.445
Aah!

01:01.050 --> 01:03.152
Yeah, I want to.
I just... I don't know.

01:04.352 --> 01:05.355
Yes, I...

01:07.857 --> 01:09.659
I can't tell him. He'll freak.

01:10.160 --> 01:11.029
He will.

01:15.198 --> 01:16.532
- Who'll freak?
- What?

01:16.933 --> 01:17.936
Who's gonna freak?

01:17.937 --> 01:20.737
Oh, um, someone from school.
You don't know them.

01:21.737 --> 01:22.705
Are you sure?

01:22.806 --> 01:23.906
Mm-hmm.

01:25.407 --> 01:26.409
But I thought I knew all your friends.

01:26.610 --> 01:28.945
Hey, I'm sorry, Dad,
but I have a ton of schoolwork.

01:28.946 --> 01:29.680
Oh, no. Yeah.

01:34.651 --> 01:36.251
Hey, uh...

01:36.952 --> 01:38.187
You know you could
tell me anything, right?

01:38.288 --> 01:38.922
Yep.

01:44.060 --> 01:44.994
Castle.

01:47.397 --> 01:48.731
A body falls out of the sky,

01:48.832 --> 01:50.634
and somehow that's my fault?

01:50.835 --> 01:51.735
Ugh!

01:52.235 --> 01:53.169
Hey, Castle.

01:54.070 --> 01:56.138
I hope we didn't take you away
from something important

01:56.539 --> 01:57.507
or someone.

01:58.308 --> 01:59.875
Did you ever keep secrets
from your Dad?

02:00.776 --> 02:01.376
Sure.

02:01.677 --> 02:02.878
What kind?

02:03.479 --> 02:04.480
Do you really want to know?

02:04.781 --> 02:06.182
About your secrets?
Absolutely?

02:06.483 --> 02:08.717
About my daughter's? Mm.

02:09.018 --> 02:10.919
You know what?
I'm sure it's nothing.

02:10.919 --> 02:12.522
Alexis would never keep
anything serious from me.

02:12.523 --> 02:14.424
- I'm the cool Dad.
- Uh-huh.

02:16.593 --> 02:18.962
- Sir, what are you doing here?
- The victim's Jack Buckley.

02:19.763 --> 02:20.632
Who's Jack Buckley?

02:20.933 --> 02:22.933
An assistant District Attorney.
One of the good guys.

02:23.433 --> 02:24.633
Buckley hated making deals,

02:24.634 --> 02:25.935
Loved putting bad guys behind bars.

02:26.736 --> 02:30.272
He's the lawyer every cop
wanted prosecuting their case.

02:31.073 --> 02:33.175
Well, looks like he didn't
go down without a fight.

02:33.476 --> 02:35.111
Yeah, his jacket was torn.

02:35.912 --> 02:37.613
We found his briefcase
up on the roof

02:37.814 --> 02:39.348
Along with his left shoe.

02:39.749 --> 02:41.051
CSU is doing a full sweep.

02:41.252 --> 02:44.453
Well, Jack's a big boy.
Whoever did it must be strong.

02:44.754 --> 02:45.822
Wait. I know what this is.

02:46.323 --> 02:48.491
Lawyer puts criminal in jail.
Criminal feels wronged.

02:48.492 --> 02:50.026
Criminal kills lawyer.
This is "Cape Fear."

02:52.227 --> 02:53.831
Any idea what he was doing up there?

02:53.932 --> 02:55.732
No, I talked to his secretary,

02:55.832 --> 02:57.499
she said Buckley
left work around 8:00,

02:57.800 --> 02:59.869
heading straight home,
which is on the West Side.

02:59.870 --> 03:01.170
And get this.

03:01.270 --> 03:03.406
Buckley was a subway rider.
He didn't own a car.

03:03.507 --> 03:04.307
Then what's he doing

03:04.407 --> 03:05.576
at a parking garage
on the East Side?

03:06.477 --> 03:07.277
That's a good question.

03:07.977 --> 03:09.278
Was Buckley married?

03:09.379 --> 03:11.647
Divorced. Ex-wife lives in California.

03:12.148 --> 03:14.249
Reach out to his wife.
Let's start looking

03:14.250 --> 03:16.118
into his personal life
and see what we can find.

03:16.319 --> 03:17.720
The Mayor wants this solved quickly.

03:17.921 --> 03:20.590
Nobody kills a law enforcement
officer and gets away with it.

03:24.527 --> 03:26.162
I just can't believe that he's dead.

03:26.563 --> 03:29.598
And you have no idea
why he was in the garage?

03:29.599 --> 03:30.701
No.

03:30.702 --> 03:33.402
Uh, here are the printouts of
Mr. Buckley's cases you wanted.

03:33.502 --> 03:34.403
Thanks.

03:34.404 --> 03:35.805
I'm telling, you this "Cape Fear" list

03:35.806 --> 03:37.707
is gonna be a gold mine of suspects.

03:37.708 --> 03:39.709
Check out this guy... Archibald Spinks.

03:40.010 --> 03:41.711
Five counts of attempted murder,

03:41.812 --> 03:43.780
One count of indecent exposure.

03:44.381 --> 03:46.249
You don't suppose he tried
to kill 'em with his...

03:46.550 --> 03:47.617
Yeah, that wouldn't work.

03:48.518 --> 03:49.919
Had Mr. Buckley ever received
any threats,

03:49.920 --> 03:51.922
any prosecutions that went ugly?

03:51.923 --> 03:53.623
Well, he didn't think
he was doing his job right

03:53.723 --> 03:56.559
if he wasn't being threatened,
but nothing recently, no.

03:56.760 --> 03:58.862
He did seem to be upset
the past few days.

03:59.163 --> 04:00.863
- Any idea why?
- No.

04:00.963 --> 04:03.098
You know, there was that man
the police brought in.

04:03.099 --> 04:03.668
What man?

04:03.669 --> 04:06.469
It was right after lunch
on Monday. A cop brought in

04:06.569 --> 04:08.405
a tough-looking guy in
handcuffs, took him right in

04:08.406 --> 04:10.308
to Mr. Buckley's office
and then waited outside.

04:10.309 --> 04:11.709
Yeah, we heard them yelling
through the door,

04:11.809 --> 04:13.244
and then the officer took him away.

04:13.245 --> 04:14.445
That kinda thing happen a lot?

04:14.646 --> 04:15.546
Never

04:15.745 --> 04:17.346
Do you remember the officer's name?

04:17.348 --> 04:20.284
Yeah. Frank. Uh, Frank...
Frank Curtis.

04:22.885 --> 04:23.552
Curtis doesn't remember

04:23.553 --> 04:25.154
why Buckley asked him
to bring the guy in,

04:25.155 --> 04:28.090
but he does remember his name.
John Knox.

04:28.191 --> 04:30.059
Dozens of priors.
Uniforms are bringing him in.

04:30.860 --> 04:32.595
I'm guessing this guy
isn't exactly an altar boy.

04:32.596 --> 04:34.797
You think?
Come on. Let's go.

04:36.298 --> 04:37.799
<i>You've got quite a record,
Mr. Knox.</i>

04:38.000 --> 04:39.168
<i>Your parents must be proud.</i>

04:39.169 --> 04:41.537
<i>Yeah, they hang all my
mug shots on the fridge.</i>

04:41.538 --> 04:43.173
Can we cut to the chase?

04:45.174 --> 04:46.374
Two days ago, you had an argument

04:46.474 --> 04:47.676
with Buckley in his office.

04:47.777 --> 04:48.745
Last night we found him dead.

04:48.846 --> 04:50.715
So you can understand our interest.

04:50.916 --> 04:53.516
Sure, but you're wasting your time.
I didn't kill the guy.

04:53.916 --> 04:54.783
Really?

04:54.784 --> 04:56.919
Because it says here
that you have quite a history

04:56.920 --> 04:59.922
of trying to kill people...
three in the last two years,

04:59.923 --> 05:03.292
- Or am I missing any?
- I was never convicted of anything.

05:03.493 --> 05:04.960
That's not exactly a denial.

05:05.661 --> 05:07.062
Do you work out?

05:07.163 --> 05:09.298
You know, bench press, dead lift?

05:10.199 --> 05:11.700
It must take
a lot of upper body strength

05:11.701 --> 05:12.702
to throw a guy off a roof.

05:12.703 --> 05:14.903
Who is this guy?

05:15.104 --> 05:16.506
What did you and Buckley fight about?

05:16.807 --> 05:19.442
Look, he had it out for me
because he put me on trial

05:19.443 --> 05:22.311
for an assault I didn't commit
and he lost.

05:22.512 --> 05:24.014
And rather than being a man about it,

05:24.015 --> 05:25.882
he decided to rattle my cage,

05:25.883 --> 05:28.184
to show me who was the alpha male.

05:28.385 --> 05:30.920
So, yeah, it was annoying
and childish,

05:30.921 --> 05:34.656
but not something you kill
a guy over, especially a DA.

05:34.657 --> 05:38.293
Now I may be a criminal,
but I'm not... stupid.

05:38.794 --> 05:41.163
Do you have an alibi
for Buckley's murder?

05:41.764 --> 05:43.232
I don't know.
What time was he killed?

05:43.433 --> 05:46.035
- 9:30 pm
- I was at an AA Meeting.

05:46.836 --> 05:49.137
Anonymous? That's cute.

05:49.238 --> 05:51.207
- You don't believe me?
- Mnh-mnh.

05:51.608 --> 05:53.476
Well, then maybe
you'll believe my sponsor...

05:54.577 --> 05:56.413
Reverend Daniel Miller.

05:58.014 --> 05:59.548
Did you say "Reverend"?

06:02.218 --> 06:03.786
So where are we with Knox?

06:04.087 --> 06:05.387
The alibi looks solid.

06:05.588 --> 06:06.722
Castle and Beckett are interviewing

06:06.723 --> 06:07.958
the good Reverend right now.

06:08.159 --> 06:09.059
What about forensics?

06:09.159 --> 06:11.994
Looks like a bust, but I did
find something interesting

06:11.995 --> 06:14.064
when checked into Buckley's
Metro card history.

06:14.265 --> 06:16.866
His card only made two swipes
a day for the whole month...

06:16.867 --> 06:19.335
6:00 am at the subway by his apartment,

06:19.336 --> 06:20.305
8:00 pm by his office.

06:20.406 --> 06:22.506
Buckley lived for the job,
especially after the divorce.

06:23.006 --> 06:24.608
Probably trying to
lose himself in the work.

06:24.609 --> 06:26.609
On the day he was killed,
Buckley did something unusual.

06:26.709 --> 06:29.610
He made an extra trip
up to West 77th Street

06:29.611 --> 06:30.312
before he went to work.

06:30.313 --> 06:32.482
- His secretary has no idea why.
- See if you can find out.

06:32.583 --> 06:35.617
Yo, cap. Looks like somebody
was following our boy Buckley.

06:35.818 --> 06:37.620
The doorman in his apartment
said that a guy

06:37.621 --> 06:40.256
came in there two days ago
demanding to talk to Buckley,

06:40.257 --> 06:41.358
wouldn't take no for an answer.

06:41.459 --> 06:43.461
Doorman practically had to
throw the guy out.

06:43.662 --> 06:46.697
Then on the morning of Buckley's
murder, the doorman swears

06:46.698 --> 06:49.500
that he saw the same guy hanging
around outside the building.

06:50.001 --> 06:52.071
I snagged a photo
off the video surveillance.

06:53.872 --> 06:55.472
Start looking through
some mug shot books.

06:58.474 --> 06:59.474
Thank you, Reverend.

06:59.875 --> 07:00.976
- Pleasure meeting you.
- Thanks.

07:02.677 --> 07:03.645
Is this for our case?

07:04.246 --> 07:06.782
Yeah, the guy who tried to
hassle Buckley at his building.

07:06.783 --> 07:09.284
Wait a second. I know this guy.

07:09.585 --> 07:11.287
Yes. My "Cape Fear" file.

07:11.288 --> 07:12.289
Ow!

07:12.990 --> 07:16.258
Right here. Right... Here.

07:16.759 --> 07:19.093
His name is Norman Jessup.

07:20.094 --> 07:21.396
Buckley got him four years ago

07:21.397 --> 07:23.065
on a bank robbery
where a guard got shot.

07:24.066 --> 07:26.101
See? I told you this file
would solve this case.

07:26.502 --> 07:28.270
It says here he got out
two weeks ago

07:28.271 --> 07:29.805
when his conviction was overturned

07:29.806 --> 07:31.441
by the Appellate Court on a technicality.

07:31.942 --> 07:34.077
That sounds like a reason
for Jessup to celebrate

07:34.078 --> 07:35.012
not to kill Buckley.

07:35.213 --> 07:37.513
Yeah, except Buckley already filed

07:37.613 --> 07:38.814
an intent to retry.

07:39.015 --> 07:41.483
Jessup was looking
at another two years in jail

07:41.484 --> 07:42.153
if Buckley won.

07:42.454 --> 07:44.554
Well, that might have
made Jessup a little mad.

07:44.654 --> 07:45.588
Right, and then it's all...

07:45.589 --> 07:48.058
"come out,
come out wherever you are."

07:48.459 --> 07:50.493
Really?
That's your de Niro?

07:50.594 --> 07:53.195
Get a current address
and a list of known associates.

07:53.196 --> 07:54.998
I'd like to hear
what Jessup has to say.

07:56.399 --> 07:58.266
Wait. Wait.
You got it all wrong.

07:59.403 --> 08:00.203
Hey!

08:00.303 --> 08:01.672
Come on! Police! Break it up!

08:03.473 --> 08:04.341
Are you gonna do something?

08:05.142 --> 08:07.142
Breaking up a bar fight
is a sure way to get hit.

08:07.342 --> 08:08.877
Don't worry.
It'll be over in a minute.

08:09.278 --> 08:10.779
You know, I was
in a bar fight once.

08:10.880 --> 08:11.914
Really? Who won?

08:11.915 --> 08:13.318
Ow! Ah!

08:13.319 --> 08:14.319
Oh, let me guess.

08:15.819 --> 08:16.620
Not you.

08:18.921 --> 08:20.391
You want to fight, Mr. Jessup?

08:20.392 --> 08:22.092
You can fight a murder charge.

08:23.892 --> 08:28.827
<font color=#7FFFO0>♫ Castle 2x09 ♫</font>
<font color=#FFFFO0>Love Me Dead</font>
Original Air Date on November 16, 2009

08:30.454 --> 08:31.221
Yo, I'm sorry, man.

08:31.222 --> 08:32.190
I didn't mean to embarrass you

08:32.191 --> 08:33.193
In front of your girlfriend there.

08:33.494 --> 08:36.193
I am not his girlfriend.
I am a Homicide Detective.

08:36.794 --> 08:39.195
and you should be taking this
a little bit more seriously.

08:39.196 --> 08:41.498
Hey, that guy in that bar, he
started this whole thing, okay?

08:41.499 --> 08:42.799
He thought I was
hitting on his girlfriend,

08:42.801 --> 08:44.602
and I was not
hitting on his girlfriend.

08:44.603 --> 08:45.904
It was just a big misunderstanding.

08:45.905 --> 08:47.905
Right. Just like the bank robbery.

08:48.005 --> 08:50.174
Exactly.
I had no idea my buddies

08:50.175 --> 08:52.142
were gonna rob that bank...
no idea at all.

08:52.343 --> 08:54.279
They said their car broke down
and they needed a ride.

08:54.280 --> 08:56.081
<i>And I gave them a ride.</i>

08:56.382 --> 08:58.382
And that argument didn't sway Buckley?

08:58.482 --> 09:01.419
Can you believe it? He told my
lawyer that the guard got shot,

09:01.420 --> 09:02.821
and therefore, in the eyes of the law,

09:02.822 --> 09:05.357
I was just as responsible
as the guy who shot him.

09:05.358 --> 09:06.658
That must have made you angry.

09:07.158 --> 09:08.526
How'd you feel about the fact
that Buckley

09:08.527 --> 09:10.495
was gonna retry your case
and try to make you serve

09:10.596 --> 09:11.697
the final two years of your sentence?

09:11.698 --> 09:14.298
Honestly, lady?
I cried like a baby.

09:14.398 --> 09:14.901
Huh.

09:14.902 --> 09:17.902
Prison is not fun, okay?
I did not want to go back.

09:18.302 --> 09:19.471
I figured if I could
just talk to Mr. Buckley,

09:19.472 --> 09:20.840
I could let him know
where I'm coming from.

09:20.841 --> 09:23.841
Which is what you were doing
at Buckley's building.

09:23.941 --> 09:27.310
Whoa. Whoa. I followed the man
around for a few days, okay?

09:27.311 --> 09:29.281
Just so I could get
my courage up to talk to him.

09:29.282 --> 09:30.882
You were stalking Buckley?

09:31.782 --> 09:33.517
Stalking is a pretty damn ugly word.

09:33.618 --> 09:34.785
Let's not use stalking, okay?

09:34.786 --> 09:35.920
I was just trying
to feel the guy out.

09:35.921 --> 09:37.856
You know what I mean? Trying to
convince him, you know?

09:37.857 --> 09:38.724
In case you guys haven't noticed,

09:38.725 --> 09:40.861
I'm somewhat of a wordsmith,
you know?

09:40.862 --> 09:44.230
A real master of,
you know, of, uh...

09:44.431 --> 09:45.431
Words?

09:46.431 --> 09:48.631
Where were you between 9:00
and 10:00 last night?

09:48.632 --> 09:50.934
I was sitting in the bar
you guys just dragged me out of.

09:50.935 --> 09:53.236
Okay. Well, we're gonna
check into your alibi.

09:53.237 --> 09:55.071
In the meantime, you're going
back into holding

09:55.072 --> 09:56.541
until we can process you for assault.

09:56.742 --> 09:59.278
Oh, oh, come on!
I said I was sorry.

09:59.279 --> 10:00.979
Wait. Buckley's mystery trip.

10:01.179 --> 10:04.114
Were you following Buckley
uptown yesterday morning?

10:04.115 --> 10:05.049
Yeah, yeah, I was.

10:06.250 --> 10:07.751
- Where did he go?
- He met some asian dude

10:07.752 --> 10:10.054
outside this real fancy
apartment building.

10:10.255 --> 10:11.889
Then they started to argue
with each other.

10:13.690 --> 10:15.325
<i>You think maybe that's
the guy who killed him?</i>

10:15.526 --> 10:17.828
Would you recognize the building
if you saw it again?

10:17.929 --> 10:19.497
Oh, yeah. I get around.

10:21.298 --> 10:22.399
Road trip.

10:22.400 --> 10:26.169
♪♪

10:26.770 --> 10:28.572
Hey, you guys mind
if I take these things off?

10:29.173 --> 10:30.441
I'm starting to feel like a stereotype

10:30.442 --> 10:32.011
riding around in the back
of a police car wearing 'em.

10:32.312 --> 10:33.512
Sure. Do you want my key?

10:34.612 --> 10:37.181
No. I got it. Thanks.

10:41.885 --> 10:42.819
How did you do that?

10:42.820 --> 10:44.788
I've always
been good with locks.

10:45.089 --> 10:47.257
When I was in the joint,
I was thinking,

10:47.258 --> 10:50.160
how can I take this and make it
more productive, you know?

10:50.261 --> 10:51.929
So I been applying
to locksmith schools.

10:52.430 --> 10:54.998
But, you know, they won't let me
in on account that I'm a felon.

10:55.099 --> 10:56.034
Can you believe that?

10:56.335 --> 10:57.935
A felon who wants to be a locksmith.

10:58.035 --> 10:59.271
What could possibly go wrong there?

10:59.672 --> 11:00.972
You don't have to be mean about it.

11:01.072 --> 11:02.440
Yeah, wow.

11:03.541 --> 11:05.008
♪♪

11:08.779 --> 11:10.414
If you're gonna be a locksmith,
you gotta listen.

11:10.415 --> 11:12.651
Left to right,
right over left.

11:12.652 --> 11:13.952
I think I made it tighter.

11:14.152 --> 11:14.919
Jessup,

11:15.320 --> 11:16.120
do you see the building?

11:16.220 --> 11:17.155
Uh, that's a negative.

11:18.655 --> 11:19.455
Now bring it around...

11:19.456 --> 11:20.524
Beckett.

11:21.425 --> 11:24.295
Oh, hey. Alexis. Uh, are you
looking for your Dad?

11:26.296 --> 11:27.197
To me?

11:27.498 --> 11:28.332
Okay, what's up?

11:29.033 --> 11:31.634
Yeah, yeah. We can meet
at Sutton's around 7:30.

11:31.635 --> 11:32.536
Is that okay?

11:33.237 --> 11:34.105
All right,
I'll see you then.

11:35.306 --> 11:36.740
Was that Alexis calling you? Why?

11:37.341 --> 11:38.408
She needed my advice.

11:38.709 --> 11:39.744
About what?

11:40.645 --> 11:43.081
I don't know.
It's probably no big deal.

11:45.282 --> 11:46.683
When you kept secrets
from your father,

11:46.684 --> 11:47.785
was it not a big deal?

11:50.386 --> 11:51.989
You know,
I'm not even gonna ask.

11:53.690 --> 11:54.991
That's the building
on the right-hand side.

11:54.992 --> 11:56.127
- Right there.
- Okay.

11:56.428 --> 11:57.063
Let's go get 'em.

11:57.264 --> 11:58.864
Not you. Us.

12:00.164 --> 12:02.399
Apartment 801?
- Okay. Thanks.

12:03.400 --> 12:04.368
So it turns out that the building's

12:04.369 --> 12:06.738
only asian tenant is Paul Cho,

12:06.839 --> 12:09.706
who just happens to be
Buckley's ex-brother-in-law.

12:09.707 --> 12:12.076
Oh, well, maybe it's not "Cape Fear" then.

12:12.077 --> 12:14.912
Maybe it's "Family Feud."
maybe Buckley's bitter divorce

12:14.913 --> 12:17.281
caused enough hard feelings
that things turned violent?

12:22.719 --> 12:25.622
I don't understand.
I haven't seen Jack in months.

12:26.123 --> 12:27.658
Not since he divorced my sister.

12:28.259 --> 12:29.492
Really?

12:29.493 --> 12:30.961
Because I have an eyewitness

12:30.962 --> 12:33.597
who saw the two of you arguing
yesterday morning.

12:34.198 --> 12:36.268
So that means you're lying to me.

12:36.469 --> 12:38.069
She hates being lied to.

12:38.169 --> 12:39.903
I don't know
what you're talking about.

12:40.004 --> 12:41.739
Great. Let's go down
to the precinct.

12:41.740 --> 12:42.574
I'll arrange a perp walk,

12:42.575 --> 12:44.377
and you can put on
a show for the cameras.

12:45.178 --> 12:46.278
Love a good perp walk.

12:46.978 --> 12:48.046
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

12:52.950 --> 12:54.017
The night before last,

12:54.018 --> 12:55.920
I was attacked by a man
in a ski mask.

12:56.621 --> 12:59.289
He warned me to tell Buckley
to back off Danton

12:59.290 --> 13:00.358
or he would ruin me.

13:00.859 --> 13:01.859
Who's Danton?

13:01.959 --> 13:04.027
I don't know,
but Jack definitely knew him.

13:04.328 --> 13:06.430
He said he wasn't gonna
let him get away with this.

13:06.831 --> 13:08.066
That's why we were fighting.

13:09.067 --> 13:10.703
I told Jack to listen
for once in his life.

13:11.504 --> 13:13.905
- He had to protect me.
- From what?

13:14.606 --> 13:16.207
That's none of your business.

13:16.408 --> 13:17.608
Perp walk it is.

13:17.708 --> 13:18.643
All right, all right.

13:20.744 --> 13:22.512
I have a...

13:22.913 --> 13:24.515
slight fondness...

13:25.916 --> 13:27.152
for girls.

13:30.053 --> 13:31.254
Young girls?

13:33.190 --> 13:34.524
Fat girls?

13:37.628 --> 13:40.296
Schoolgirls?

13:40.797 --> 13:42.165
Call girls.

13:42.166 --> 13:43.466
Oh.

13:43.966 --> 13:45.869
Who else knows about this fondness?

13:46.270 --> 13:47.371
Just the girls.

13:47.372 --> 13:50.907
Actually, the girls... and their pimp.

13:51.808 --> 13:54.377
Whose name is probably Danton.

13:54.378 --> 13:56.880
O-okay, fine.
But I wasn't really lying.

13:56.881 --> 13:59.117
I-I've actually never met Danton.

13:59.118 --> 14:02.486
Uh, I got the phone number
for the Agency from a friend.

14:02.487 --> 14:04.789
I call it, and they send over a girl.

14:06.590 --> 14:10.693
So Buckley is investigating
Danton's call girl ring.

14:10.894 --> 14:11.895
When Danton discovers

14:11.896 --> 14:13.397
that Buckley's brother-in-law
is a client,

14:13.398 --> 14:16.200
he sends a message... back off
or your family gets hurt.

14:16.201 --> 14:18.135
And then when Buckley
doesn't back down,

14:18.136 --> 14:19.603
Danton kills him.

14:20.004 --> 14:21.505
So how do we find Danton?

14:22.506 --> 14:23.609
We talk to one of the call girls.

14:27.812 --> 14:30.014
Call that number and tell him
to bring one of his girls over.

14:30.215 --> 14:32.417
And tell her to wear something sexy.

14:34.318 --> 14:36.220
No reason we can't enjoy
this interview.

14:41.158 --> 14:42.058
Hey, Paul.

14:42.059 --> 14:43.827
Couldn't wait to see me, huh?

14:49.600 --> 14:51.368
Actually, I'm the one
who asked for the date.

14:52.769 --> 14:54.704
Isn't that the girl
from Buckley's office?

14:56.474 --> 14:58.175
Did she look like that before?

15:04.876 --> 15:06.710
So how exactly does a call girl

15:06.711 --> 15:08.812
end up working for
Jack Buckley, super DA?

15:09.313 --> 15:10.647
Am I under arrest?

15:10.648 --> 15:12.650
You will be if you don't
answer the question.

15:14.451 --> 15:16.186
Jack was a client.

15:17.187 --> 15:19.022
I-I'm sorry, Scarlett.
I don't believe that.

15:19.523 --> 15:21.992
I started seeing him about a year ago.

15:22.993 --> 15:24.928
He hadn't been with anyone
since his divorce.

15:25.929 --> 15:28.232
He was just lonely, you know?

15:29.433 --> 15:31.436
We'd spend
most of his dates talking.

15:33.337 --> 15:34.871
He'd take me to fancy restaurants...

15:35.672 --> 15:38.041
Even though I told him
he didn't have to.

15:38.842 --> 15:40.243
But I think he wanted
to make it feel

15:40.244 --> 15:41.779
as normal as possible.

15:43.380 --> 15:44.981
Then one night, he saw...

15:44.982 --> 15:47.117
a law book in my bag.

15:48.118 --> 15:51.455
I told him I was only
working as an escort

15:51.456 --> 15:53.590
to pay my way through law school.

15:54.591 --> 15:57.460
A few months later, he said
he had an internship

15:57.461 --> 15:59.096
opening up in his office.

16:01.097 --> 16:02.332
Would I be interested?

16:03.633 --> 16:05.770
He wanted to help you escape the life?

16:07.371 --> 16:08.571
Who's Danton?

16:08.872 --> 16:11.374
- I don't know.
- Don't lie to us, Scarlett.

16:11.375 --> 16:12.309
I'm not.

16:13.210 --> 16:16.613
I-I know he runs the business,
but I've never met him.

16:17.014 --> 16:19.149
It's not like I'm a streetwalker

16:19.150 --> 16:22.452
and he's in a fedora
and a long fur coat.

16:22.753 --> 16:25.521
He's organized the entire operation

16:25.622 --> 16:27.257
to protect his identity.

16:27.758 --> 16:29.693
The girls are independent contractors.

16:29.994 --> 16:31.995
The clients are all given numbers

16:31.996 --> 16:33.531
so we don't know their last names.

16:34.332 --> 16:36.300
They pay the business by credit card.

16:37.301 --> 16:41.804
And our fees get deposited
directly into our bank accounts.

16:41.805 --> 16:43.306
Creating the perfect firewall

16:43.307 --> 16:44.808
between the girls and the management.

16:44.809 --> 16:47.344
So then when we arrest you,
you can't give up Danton.

16:48.245 --> 16:49.946
Because I don't know who he is.

16:55.986 --> 16:58.021
I can't believe Jack Buckley
was seeing prostitutes.

16:58.722 --> 17:01.056
Yeah, well, he worked
14 hours a day,

17:01.057 --> 17:02.225
didn't have a social life.

17:03.226 --> 17:04.961
Maybe he just wanted
a little easy company.

17:05.362 --> 17:07.330
Well, the math
just doesn't add up, though.

17:08.432 --> 17:10.333
Buckley was warned to back off Danton.

17:10.434 --> 17:11.834
Why would Buckley be investigating

17:11.835 --> 17:13.470
a call girl service he was using?

17:13.971 --> 17:16.705
Maybe Danton tried to blackmail
Buckley, and it backfired.

17:17.406 --> 17:20.510
So then Danton
tried to scare Buckley

17:21.011 --> 17:22.412
by threatening his brother-in-law.

17:22.413 --> 17:24.348
And then when that didn't work,
Danton killed Buckley.

17:24.348 --> 17:26.549
All right. Let's find out everything
we can about this Danton character.

17:26.617 --> 17:28.653
Have Ryan and Esposito reach out
to Vice in the morning.

17:28.654 --> 17:29.654
Yes, sir.

17:30.354 --> 17:32.823
Castle, I need you to sign
these charges against Jessup

17:32.824 --> 17:33.992
so I can send him downtown.

17:38.528 --> 17:39.862
What?

17:41.465 --> 17:43.499
No, don't tell me you've got
a soft spot for this guy.

17:43.800 --> 17:44.969
He's a wordsmith.

17:46.370 --> 17:48.271
Okay. Fine.

17:49.807 --> 17:50.907
Hi, it's Beckett.

17:51.108 --> 17:53.076
Uh, charges are being dropped
against Jessup.

17:53.077 --> 17:54.046
Process him out.

17:54.247 --> 17:55.347
All right. Thank you.

17:56.847 --> 17:59.183
I hope the two of you
are very happy together.

18:03.319 --> 18:04.120
Are you okay?

18:04.721 --> 18:07.090
No. I... broke a heel.

18:07.991 --> 18:08.692
Let me guess.

18:08.693 --> 18:10.427
They were your favorite pair,

18:10.728 --> 18:12.729
passed through your family
for generations.

18:13.930 --> 18:15.898
My great-great-grandmother
wore them over

18:15.899 --> 18:16.799
on the "Mayflower."

18:16.900 --> 18:17.669
I knew it.

18:19.970 --> 18:21.938
So what's a nice girl like you...

18:22.939 --> 18:25.175
Really?
That's your line?

18:25.476 --> 18:26.410
I'm old-fashioned.

18:28.811 --> 18:32.248
I came to New York
in this ancient blue Beetle.

18:32.549 --> 18:33.718
The floor was so rusted,

18:33.719 --> 18:35.820
it literally sagged in the middle.

18:36.221 --> 18:39.756
But I can still remember
coming over the bridge

18:39.757 --> 18:42.859
and seeing the city
right there in front of me.

18:43.060 --> 18:45.895
I thought everything
was gonna be perfect.

18:46.296 --> 18:48.866
Something tells me this story
takes a turn for the worse.

18:49.767 --> 18:52.702
The first night, uh,
somebody broke into my car

18:52.803 --> 18:55.238
and stole all my stuff.

18:55.639 --> 18:58.907
Then the college friend
I was gonna stay with

18:58.908 --> 19:01.177
told me her boyfriend was moving in.

19:01.178 --> 19:03.846
- I had to find another place.
- Ooh.

19:03.947 --> 19:06.082
But somehow, I survived.

19:06.783 --> 19:08.551
Spent a year barely eating,

19:08.852 --> 19:10.086
living in a closet.

19:10.787 --> 19:12.388
When a friend mentioned doing this,

19:12.389 --> 19:15.525
I thought... couldn't be worse.

19:16.626 --> 19:17.760
And is it?

19:19.261 --> 19:20.396
Mostly no.

19:24.701 --> 19:26.169
Thanks for listening.

19:32.542 --> 19:33.877
Good night, Castle.

19:34.378 --> 19:36.079
- You going to meet Alexis?
- Yeah.

19:36.080 --> 19:36.715
Can I come?

19:38.216 --> 19:38.816
No.

19:38.916 --> 19:40.050
But I want to.

19:41.251 --> 19:42.752
Why are you so worried, Castle?

19:42.753 --> 19:44.322
I thought you were the cool Dad.

19:47.323 --> 19:48.559
I am.

19:54.130 --> 19:55.131
What's the secret?

19:55.732 --> 19:57.367
All in the breathing, dear.

19:57.968 --> 19:59.268
No, what's Alexis' secret

19:59.269 --> 20:00.970
that she'll tell Beckett about
but not me?

20:00.971 --> 20:03.306
I don't know.
There are some things a woman

20:03.507 --> 20:05.609
wants to talk to another woman about.

20:05.610 --> 20:06.410
The "New York Times"

20:06.510 --> 20:08.645
praised the depth
of my female characters.

20:08.746 --> 20:11.314
I know. And I couldn't be prouder.

20:11.515 --> 20:12.682
But this is real life.

20:12.683 --> 20:15.284
And obviously,
Alexis looks up to Beckett.

20:15.285 --> 20:17.554
And Beckett's smart and strong
and independent.

20:17.555 --> 20:18.455
So are you.

20:18.555 --> 20:20.356
That's sweet. Mm.

20:20.557 --> 20:22.258
I'm on the wrong side of 40

20:22.259 --> 20:23.994
for what Alexis
is going through right now.

20:24.295 --> 20:25.195
40?

20:25.295 --> 20:26.563
Deflect all you want, kiddo,

20:26.564 --> 20:28.565
but I recognize the fear in your eyes.

20:28.766 --> 20:31.202
You're afraid Alexis has
more Rick Castle in her

20:31.203 --> 20:31.939
than you thought.

20:33.440 --> 20:36.440
Hey, sweetie. How did
your talk with Beckett, go?

20:36.640 --> 20:38.241
Fine. She's really nice.

20:38.542 --> 20:40.143
Yeah, she is.

20:41.244 --> 20:42.645
You know, sweetheart,
if you don't want to tell me

20:42.646 --> 20:44.282
what you talked about
with Beckett, you don't have to.

20:44.583 --> 20:46.083
Okay. Thanks, dad.

20:48.652 --> 20:51.187
What is the matter with you?

20:51.188 --> 20:52.522
Why didn't you just ask her?

20:52.523 --> 20:55.825
Because that would be prying,
and cool dads don't do that.

20:56.226 --> 20:57.594
They go behind
their daughter's back,

20:57.595 --> 20:58.696
and they beg Beckett to tell 'em.

21:02.199 --> 21:04.534
- You ever have any cases with Buckley?
- A few.

21:04.535 --> 21:06.203
Guy was wound a little tight
if you ask me.

21:06.304 --> 21:08.405
Saw himself
as a crusader for justice.

21:08.506 --> 21:09.807
Yo, Esposito.

21:10.008 --> 21:11.608
Gil Mazzara.
What's up, man?

21:11.708 --> 21:12.577
How you doing?

21:12.578 --> 21:14.378
So you still looking at
dirty pictures up in Vice?

21:14.478 --> 21:16.280
Yeah, tell your mom
to send over some new ones.

21:16.281 --> 21:17.483
The ones I got are getting old.

21:18.284 --> 21:19.286
You know my partner... Ryan?

21:19.987 --> 21:22.687
Yeah. Honey milk.
Nice to see you.

21:23.287 --> 21:26.055
So, uh, I hear you're
looking to talk about Danton.

21:26.456 --> 21:28.325
- Yeah. You know him?
- Yeah, I arrested him five years ago.

21:28.326 --> 21:30.326
Real name's Dan Tonelli.

21:30.527 --> 21:32.061
Dan-ton.

21:32.062 --> 21:33.197
- Yeah.
- He's currently serving

21:33.198 --> 21:35.332
a 7-year stretch
in Green Haven Correctional.

21:35.933 --> 21:37.334
Wait a minute.
He's still in prison?

21:37.735 --> 21:39.503
And your boy Buckley put him there.

21:39.704 --> 21:40.804
Buckley prosecuted Danton?

21:41.104 --> 21:43.906
Yeah. And he was all over us
to make a rock-solid case.

21:44.407 --> 21:46.810
We gave Buckley enough to put
the guy away for 20 years.

21:47.811 --> 21:49.480
Could Tonelli still be running
the operation out of prison?

21:49.481 --> 21:50.481
Nah.

21:50.781 --> 21:52.882
These call girl rings
are like franchises.

21:52.983 --> 21:55.218
The business changes hands,
but the name stays the same.

21:55.619 --> 21:56.819
So who's the new Danton?

21:57.220 --> 21:59.622
I wish I knew.
Guy's like a ghost.

22:00.123 --> 22:02.325
Every time we think we're
getting close, he disappears.

22:02.726 --> 22:05.428
Five warrants in the last year,
and every time we show up,

22:05.429 --> 22:07.399
the place has been cleared out
like he knew we were coming.

22:07.400 --> 22:09.300
You call the prison. Get 'em
to bring Tonelli over here.

