contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

22:18.308 --> 22:19.676
Hey. You guys seen Beckett?

22:20.177 --> 22:22.745
She went with the Captain
to update City Hall on the case.

22:22.746 --> 22:23.947
She'll be here in a minute.

22:24.348 --> 22:25.148
Something wrong?

22:25.248 --> 22:26.850
No. Yes.

22:27.951 --> 22:30.653
I think my daughter might be
keeping something from me.

22:30.854 --> 22:32.255
Maybe she got kicked outta school.

22:32.256 --> 22:33.056
What?

22:33.156 --> 22:36.258
- Or she's doing drugs.
- Mm-hmm. Teen pregnancy is on the rise.

22:36.359 --> 22:38.795
Whoa. All right,
you've met my daughter.

22:38.896 --> 22:40.864
You know that she is
the closest thing to perfect

22:40.865 --> 22:41.799
as humanly possible.

22:42.800 --> 22:45.502
Castle, come on. You've been
with us long enough to know

22:45.503 --> 22:47.004
that people are never
who you think they are.

22:47.105 --> 22:49.039
Isn't it possible
your perfect daughter

22:49.040 --> 22:50.642
Isn't as perfect as you think?

22:50.943 --> 22:52.343
Is Danton here yet?

22:52.643 --> 22:54.010
Yep. Interrogation room one.

22:54.811 --> 22:55.879
Wait, Danton?

22:56.180 --> 22:57.482
Come on, Castle. Keep up.

22:59.583 --> 23:01.952
We brought you in here
to talk about Danton.

23:02.653 --> 23:03.853
Ancient history.

23:04.054 --> 23:06.789
It says here, Buckley made
a plea deal with you...

23:06.790 --> 23:08.291
7 years instead of 20.

23:08.292 --> 23:10.793
But I heard
Buckley doesn't make deals.

23:11.094 --> 23:12.662
What could I say? I got lucky.

23:12.963 --> 23:15.597
The only reason that Buckley
would agree to a deal

23:15.598 --> 23:17.600
is because you brought him
something big in return.

23:17.801 --> 23:18.734
So what was it?

23:18.935 --> 23:20.070
Why don't you ask him?

23:20.471 --> 23:21.471
Because he's dead.

23:21.871 --> 23:23.839
What? How?

23:23.840 --> 23:25.875
He was murdered two nights ago.

23:26.076 --> 23:29.111
We believe that the same person
who took over your operations killed him.

23:31.948 --> 23:32.916
What's so funny?

23:33.117 --> 23:35.686
Well, you see, that would
make it a suicide.

23:35.987 --> 23:37.087
Suicide?

23:37.788 --> 23:41.288
Wait a minute. You're saying that
Jack Buckley was the new Danton?

23:42.425 --> 23:43.593
Buckley made me a deal.

23:43.994 --> 23:46.797
I provide him with
my client list, my girls,

23:46.898 --> 23:48.732
he knocks 13 years off my sentence.

23:48.733 --> 23:50.103
It was a no-brainer.

23:50.804 --> 23:52.404
Our DA was a pimp.

23:55.083 --> 23:56.183
Jack Buckley was Danton.

23:56.484 --> 23:58.185
That's why all vice's warrants failed.

23:58.486 --> 23:59.854
They had to go through the DA's office,

23:59.855 --> 24:00.788
and Buckley saw them coming.

24:00.789 --> 24:02.957
He was in the perfect position
to protect his operation.

24:03.358 --> 24:07.060
But why would a respected
prosecutor become a pimp?

24:07.061 --> 24:08.095
The outfits.

24:08.496 --> 24:09.596
It was the money.

24:10.296 --> 24:11.964
Buckley's ex-wife
took him to the cleaners.

24:11.965 --> 24:13.766
Between alimony and his own bills,

24:13.767 --> 24:15.168
Buckley was beyond broke.

24:15.469 --> 24:17.370
You know what? I'm bettin' it was
more than just the money.

24:17.671 --> 24:20.206
Everybody's talking about
how great Jack Buckley was,

24:20.307 --> 24:21.808
<i>How he was the law.</i>

24:21.909 --> 24:22.943
You start thinking like that,

24:23.944 --> 24:26.647
sometimes you can start thinking
maybe you are above the law,

24:26.848 --> 24:28.116
that you can get away with anything.

24:29.717 --> 24:31.119
Sir, how did the Mayor handle the news?

24:31.120 --> 24:32.520
Whew. You don't want to know.

24:33.120 --> 24:35.288
Okay, this doesn't make any sense.

24:35.689 --> 24:39.191
If Buckley was the new Danton,
then why would the masked man

24:39.192 --> 24:40.760
tell Buckley to back off of Danton?

24:40.761 --> 24:42.362
Buckley wouldn't threaten himself.

24:45.198 --> 24:46.833
Unless Buckley wasn't the boss anymore.

24:46.834 --> 24:48.602
- A hostile takeover.
- Of course.

24:48.903 --> 24:51.670
We know Danton was just
a business name.

24:51.671 --> 24:53.172
So "back off of Danton"

24:53.273 --> 24:54.941
was the new boss telling the old boss,

24:55.142 --> 24:56.543
"don't resist the takeover

24:56.544 --> 24:57.846
or I'll start ruining reputations."

24:57.847 --> 24:59.547
Makes sense in theory,
but how do you prove it?

25:00.447 --> 25:01.715
We talk to the call girl.

25:04.484 --> 25:05.385
There is no way

25:05.386 --> 25:07.721
that Scarlett didn't know
that Buckley was in charge.

25:10.991 --> 25:13.659
No, seriously, what did
Alexis tell you last night?

25:14.360 --> 25:16.195
I promised I wouldn't say.

25:16.196 --> 25:18.231
Well, at least tell me
if it was bad.

25:18.432 --> 25:19.933
And put you out of your misery?

25:23.470 --> 25:24.638
We're looking for Scarlett.

25:26.239 --> 25:28.074
We can't have call girls working here.

25:28.075 --> 25:29.276
No, only pimps.

25:30.377 --> 25:31.545
Detective.

25:33.346 --> 25:34.748
Could you give us a moment, please?

25:38.985 --> 25:40.553
Scarlett, you lied to us.

25:40.954 --> 25:42.888
Buckley was running
the call girl ring,

25:42.889 --> 25:44.458
and there's no way
that you didn't know.

25:46.159 --> 25:47.659
Please. I had to lie.

25:47.660 --> 25:49.428
He'd kill me if he thought
I told you anything.

25:49.429 --> 25:50.997
Who'd kill you, the new Danton?

25:51.098 --> 25:53.233
Someone took over Buckley's
business. Who was it?

25:54.234 --> 25:55.136
Answer me.

25:56.037 --> 25:57.437
He used to work for Buckley.

25:57.737 --> 26:00.340
He made sure no one hurt
the girls and everyone paid.

26:00.341 --> 26:01.341
What was his name?

26:01.441 --> 26:02.609
I can't tell you that.

26:02.610 --> 26:03.810
Scarlett, I'm done playing.

26:03.910 --> 26:06.112
You've done nothing but lie
to us. Don't think that I'm not

26:06.113 --> 26:07.981
gonna send you away
for obstruction of justice

26:07.982 --> 26:09.251
and anything else that I can think of.

26:09.752 --> 26:10.952
He'll kill me.

26:11.052 --> 26:12.054
We won't let that happen.

26:12.955 --> 26:14.255
Detective Beckett can help you,

26:14.355 --> 26:15.523
but you have to help us first.

26:15.724 --> 26:16.824
And then what happens to me?

26:17.624 --> 26:19.193
You think I'm gonna be a lawyer now?

26:19.594 --> 26:21.629
Jack was gonna write me
a letter of recommendation,

26:22.030 --> 26:23.364
pull some strings to get me a job.

26:23.565 --> 26:24.934
Who's gonna help me now?

26:24.935 --> 26:27.135
Honestly? No one.

26:28.235 --> 26:29.603
You're gonna have to do it
by yourself, Scarlett.

26:29.604 --> 26:30.739
And I got a feeling that you can.

26:31.540 --> 26:33.475
Tell us who the new boss is...

26:35.776 --> 26:36.977
and Detective Beckett will make sure

26:36.978 --> 26:38.613
no one knows
it was you who talked to us.

26:41.614 --> 26:42.649
You promise?

26:47.353 --> 26:48.587
Yes.

26:50.488 --> 26:51.824
His name is John Knox.

26:52.525 --> 26:54.127
Knox? But that's...

26:54.128 --> 26:56.464
The guy that Buckley
dragged in here in handcuffs.

26:58.765 --> 27:01.900
How does a prosecutor get into
business with a criminal?

27:02.701 --> 27:04.102
Well, it's hard out there
for a pimp...

27:04.403 --> 27:05.404
Who's also a DA

27:06.205 --> 27:08.041
Ooh, that'd be
a good character for a novel.

27:08.042 --> 27:08.942
Mm.

27:09.042 --> 27:10.776
A star prosecutor
who's always excelled

27:10.777 --> 27:11.778
at anything he's ever done...

27:11.979 --> 27:13.880
he couldn't possibly imagine
that being a pimp

27:13.881 --> 27:15.982
would be a bigger job
than he could handle by himself.

27:16.083 --> 27:17.251
But one day he gets a call...

27:17.352 --> 27:19.454
one of his girls has been
knocked around by a client.

27:19.955 --> 27:21.923
He realizes there's nothing
he can do about it.

27:22.024 --> 27:23.725
- He's a very public figure.
- Mm-hmm.

27:23.726 --> 27:26.327
So a white-collar prosecutor
decides to hire

27:26.328 --> 27:28.263
a blue-collared enforcer.

27:28.964 --> 27:30.766
Can't exactly take out an ad
on craigslist for that,

27:30.767 --> 27:33.734
but fortunately enough,
he has a big stack

27:33.735 --> 27:36.304
of qualified candidates
sitting right on his desk.

27:36.305 --> 27:38.205
Which is where he found John Knox,

27:38.305 --> 27:40.607
a criminal who mostly managed
to stay out of prison.

27:40.608 --> 27:42.108
Which makes him a smart criminal.

27:42.208 --> 27:43.576
- Yeah.
- Buckley offers him a deal...

27:43.677 --> 27:45.711
"come work for me,
I'll throw your case."

27:45.912 --> 27:47.246
- And Knox does.
- Mm-hmm.

27:47.247 --> 27:48.914
For a while, everyone's happy.

27:48.915 --> 27:50.216
But then Knox decides

27:50.217 --> 27:51.851
he's not happy
being number two anymore.

27:52.052 --> 27:54.787
He takes Buckley's client list,
tells Buckley to take a hike.

27:54.788 --> 27:56.722
Knowing that Buckley
can't do anything about it

27:56.723 --> 27:58.458
- without risking exposure.
- Mm-hmm.

27:58.459 --> 28:01.027
But Buckley's never backed down
from a fight in his life.

28:01.228 --> 28:03.230
He gets the cops to drag Knox
down to his office

28:03.231 --> 28:05.366
- to remind him who's boss.
- But Knox took it up a notch,

28:05.367 --> 28:07.534
sending a warning shot
across Buckley's bow

28:07.535 --> 28:10.437
- by threatening his brother-in-law.
- And when Buckley wouldn't back down,

28:10.538 --> 28:12.574
Knox threw him off the roof
of a parking garage.

28:12.975 --> 28:14.475
Jeez, if only we had some proof.

28:14.575 --> 28:16.744
Who needs proof?
What a great story.

28:17.445 --> 28:19.546
Of course, Knox has an alibi.

28:21.147 --> 28:22.115
You know, maybe you're right.

28:23.216 --> 28:26.619
Maybe Knox is smart.
Maybe he sent someone else.

28:26.720 --> 28:28.121
Ooh, I like the twist...

28:28.122 --> 28:29.889
The enforcer has an enforcer.

28:31.390 --> 28:32.191
But who?

28:32.792 --> 28:34.127
♪♪

28:34.128 --> 28:36.096
No, it worked out well.
It was good.

28:36.097 --> 28:38.532
You know, I'll talk
to you guys later, okay?

28:40.333 --> 28:42.368
Hi. Remember us?

28:42.969 --> 28:44.470
I definitely remember you.

28:44.671 --> 28:46.739
We need to ask you
a few questions.

28:46.840 --> 28:48.507
I already answered your questions.

28:48.708 --> 28:50.243
Maybe you didn't see the badge.

28:50.444 --> 28:52.178
Oh, I saw it.

28:53.279 --> 28:55.347
You ladies ready?
Excellent.

28:56.348 --> 28:57.850
You two have a nice evening.

28:57.851 --> 29:00.852
Who's hungry?
What do you guys feel like?

29:00.853 --> 29:01.988
Aren't you gonna stop him?

29:02.489 --> 29:05.391
I can't. Unless we arrest him,

29:05.392 --> 29:07.527
the law says that he doesn't
have to talk to us,

29:07.528 --> 29:09.662
- and he knows that.
- So arrest him.

29:09.663 --> 29:11.130
On what grounds?

29:11.531 --> 29:14.733
We promised Scarlett
that we'd keep her out of it.

29:15.134 --> 29:16.269
So unless we get some evidence,

29:16.270 --> 29:17.604
he's getting away with this.

29:32.118 --> 29:33.218
Scarlett?

29:34.287 --> 29:35.788
You're hurt.

29:35.889 --> 29:37.825
I didn't know where else to go.

29:42.412 --> 29:43.980
Come. Sit down.

29:47.249 --> 29:48.451
You should go to a hospital.

29:49.352 --> 29:51.487
It's just a few bruises.
I'll be fine.

29:52.188 --> 29:53.389
How did you find me?

29:54.490 --> 29:56.525
A client in the publishing business

29:56.526 --> 29:57.495
gave me your address.

29:59.796 --> 30:00.897
Dinner for one?

30:01.498 --> 30:03.699
Yeah, my family is at the theater.

30:03.700 --> 30:05.134
Good.

30:05.135 --> 30:07.738
I wouldn't want anyone else
to see me like this.

30:11.274 --> 30:12.809
Did Knox do this to you?

30:14.478 --> 30:15.578
It doesn't matter.

30:15.678 --> 30:16.612
Of course it does.

30:16.613 --> 30:18.081
Do you think that by protecting him,

30:18.082 --> 30:20.284
you're saving yourself somehow?
Because you're not.

30:21.685 --> 30:23.553
And if you don't get out
from under his thumb now,

30:23.554 --> 30:24.689
you never will.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.325
Why are you so nice to me?

30:29.426 --> 30:30.993
How do you know I'm not this nice

30:30.994 --> 30:32.863
to all the beautiful women
I find on my doorstep?

30:35.064 --> 30:36.832
You really think I'm beautiful?

30:38.033 --> 30:40.103
Look, maybe we should...

30:43.907 --> 30:45.242
- I'm sorry.
- No.

30:45.243 --> 30:47.344
- I shouldn't have done that.
- It's okay. It's...

30:49.345 --> 30:51.747
You're hurt and you're scared.

30:53.448 --> 30:55.785
But you don't have to be
that person with me.

30:57.920 --> 30:59.255
You're safe here.

31:04.660 --> 31:06.295
Knox killed Buckley.

31:06.296 --> 31:08.998
No. No, he has an alibi.

31:16.939 --> 31:17.907
The Reverend?

31:18.308 --> 31:19.942
Knox made me take it.

31:21.043 --> 31:23.145
Reverend Daniel is a client.

31:23.546 --> 31:25.881
Knox is blackmailing him into saying

31:25.882 --> 31:27.917
they were together
when Buckley was killed.

31:29.218 --> 31:30.786
Thank you.

31:31.587 --> 31:34.490
Now I'm taking you
to a hospital. No arguments.

31:34.491 --> 31:35.691
Okay.

31:38.361 --> 31:39.528
Hey.

31:39.729 --> 31:41.864
I'm thinking Knox killed Buckley.

31:42.365 --> 31:43.332
Knox has an alibi.

31:43.333 --> 31:45.134
Hmm, does he?

31:45.135 --> 31:49.238
Reverend alibi in the flesh...
lots of flesh...

31:50.239 --> 31:51.840
Too much flesh.

31:52.241 --> 31:54.310
- Where'd you get this?
- Scarlett Price.

31:54.911 --> 31:56.145
You saw her without me?

31:56.146 --> 31:57.947
Uh, well, yes.

31:57.948 --> 32:00.116
She's a person of interest
in our investigation,

32:00.117 --> 32:02.452
<i>- Our murder investigation.
- No, I know.</i>

32:02.453 --> 32:05.621
- Where'd you see her?
- Uh... My apartment.

32:05.622 --> 32:06.124
What?

32:06.125 --> 32:08.425
When I came home last night,
she was in my hall,

32:08.525 --> 32:10.393
- and somebody had beaten her up.
- And you didn't think to call me?

32:10.394 --> 32:11.328
Well, I took her to the hospital.

32:11.329 --> 32:13.698
The night kinda got away
from me, and then I came here,

32:13.699 --> 32:15.935
You know, to surprise you
like... like I do.

32:17.236 --> 32:19.036
We are not done talking about this.

32:20.736 --> 32:21.470
Esposito.

32:21.471 --> 32:23.239
- Yeah.
- Have surveillance pull in Knox.

32:23.240 --> 32:25.775
- On it.
- Whoa. You had Knox under surveillance

32:25.776 --> 32:26.512
and you didn't tell me?

32:27.113 --> 32:28.913
At least I didn't go out
on a date with him.

32:29.013 --> 32:31.214
- It wasn't a date.
- Really?

32:31.215 --> 32:33.716
Trouble.
Knox's apartment is empty.

32:33.717 --> 32:35.318
He must have slipped out
during the night.

32:35.519 --> 32:36.686
Scarlett...

32:36.687 --> 32:37.988
I left her
at St. Vincent's Hospital.

32:40.189 --> 32:42.391
Yes. Hello. I dropped a young
woman off there last night.

32:42.392 --> 32:43.827
Her name is Scarlett Price.
She'd been beaten up.

32:43.828 --> 32:45.163
I need to speak to her
right away, please.

32:46.664 --> 32:48.064
What? When?

32:48.464 --> 32:49.698
Thank you.

32:49.699 --> 32:51.335
A man checked her out
right after I left.

32:51.336 --> 32:52.436
Knox.

32:52.636 --> 32:54.203
Get a unit out to Scarlett's apartment

32:54.204 --> 32:55.306
and get an APB out on both of them.

32:59.175 --> 33:00.876
- Hello.
- He's got me.

33:00.977 --> 33:02.611
Scarlett, hang on, hang on.

33:02.612 --> 33:04.714
I think he's gonna kill me.

33:04.715 --> 33:06.616
- Where are you?
- I don't know. I...

33:06.717 --> 33:08.152
Hey, what are you doing in there?!

33:08.453 --> 33:09.453
Scarlett.

33:10.153 --> 33:11.988
What do we do?
We have to do something?

33:12.789 --> 33:14.323
Ryan, get the carrier on the phone.

33:14.424 --> 33:16.025
Let 'em know that I'm about
a minute away

33:16.026 --> 33:17.894
from getting a trace warrant
on the following number...

33:17.895 --> 33:21.229
212-555-0179.

33:21.230 --> 33:22.965
Got it.

33:22.966 --> 33:27.069
This is Detective Kate Beckett,
badge number 4-1-3-1-9.

33:27.070 --> 33:29.205
I need to talk
to Judge Beall right away.

33:29.506 --> 33:31.573
Scarlett's phone traced
to the East Side of the building.

33:31.643 --> 33:34.044
Hotel manager said that a guy
matching Knox's description

33:34.145 --> 33:36.213
checked into room 4-F this morning.

33:36.714 --> 33:38.014
Castle, you're staying here.

33:38.114 --> 33:39.250
No, I'm not.

33:42.051 --> 33:43.719
Okay, but stay behind me.

33:53.228 --> 33:54.162
Stop! No!

33:58.643 --> 34:00.211
Police!

34:07.685 --> 34:09.286
Over there. It's Knox.

34:11.856 --> 34:12.789
Scarlett.

34:13.590 --> 34:14.757
Hey. Hey.

34:14.958 --> 34:16.161
Hey, it's okay.

34:18.661 --> 34:19.862
I killed him.

34:20.164 --> 34:21.197
It's okay. You're okay.

34:21.998 --> 34:23.234
I killed Knox.

34:24.435 --> 34:26.902
He heard a noise outside,
and wh...

34:26.904 --> 34:28.906
And when he turned to look,
I grabbed his gun.

34:29.907 --> 34:32.743
He told me to give it back.
He came after me.

34:33.744 --> 34:35.647
I told him to stop, but he wouldn't.

34:37.047 --> 34:38.384
Why wouldn't he stop?

34:41.784 --> 34:43.154
Why wouldn't he stop?

34:53.731 --> 34:55.366
You think she'll be okay?

34:56.367 --> 34:57.634
Well, given the circumstances,

34:57.635 --> 34:59.202
I don't think the DA
will press charges.

34:59.503 --> 35:01.672
<i>No, I mean, do you think
she'll be okay?</i>

35:03.073 --> 35:04.207
I don't know.

35:06.010 --> 35:07.377
Girls in the sex industry

35:07.378 --> 35:10.080
usually come from a history
of childhood dysfunction.

35:10.281 --> 35:11.648
It's hard to escape that.

35:12.549 --> 35:14.084
But it's possible, right?

35:15.785 --> 35:16.753
Yeah.

35:17.554 --> 35:18.355
Hold it right there!

35:18.556 --> 35:19.890
Castle, little help?

35:20.491 --> 35:22.593
Oh, yeah. Julian, it's fine.
He's with me.

35:22.594 --> 35:23.694
You are outta control, man.

35:24.995 --> 35:27.430
I got good news. I finally
found a locksmith school

35:27.431 --> 35:28.832
- that's willing to admit me.
- Really?

35:28.833 --> 35:31.568
Yeah. All I need is a letter of
recommendation from the police,

35:31.569 --> 35:33.571
And I am in.
Will you write it for me?

35:33.572 --> 35:34.872
No!

35:34.972 --> 35:36.807
- What?
- Come on. Have a heart.

35:36.808 --> 35:39.076
He's a criminal.
If I write him a letter,

35:39.077 --> 35:41.713
I'll be responsible for him. I
cannot watch you 24 hours a day.

35:41.914 --> 35:43.014
Wait a minute.
What'd you say?

35:43.114 --> 35:44.515
I would be responsible for him.

35:44.716 --> 35:47.017
No, no, no.
You can't watch him...

35:47.218 --> 35:49.453
When did you put
the surveillance car on Knox?

35:49.454 --> 35:51.822
- Right after we left the bar.
- And they followed him all night?

35:51.823 --> 35:53.725
Yeah. He got home around 2:00 am

35:53.926 --> 35:55.426
Then how could he
have beaten up Scarlett?

35:55.826 --> 35:57.294
You guys do know that the deadbolt

35:57.295 --> 35:59.330
wasn set on this lock when
you guys kicked it in, right?

35:59.431 --> 36:00.331
What?

36:00.431 --> 36:02.666
See? If it would've been,

36:02.667 --> 36:04.301
this whole frame
would've been destroyed.

36:04.602 --> 36:07.805
Locking the door...
that's hostage taking 101.

36:09.406 --> 36:11.942
Unless Scarlett wasn't a hostage.

36:12.743 --> 36:14.412
She was in on it from the start.

36:14.413 --> 36:16.213
Buckley didn't set her up in his office

36:16.313 --> 36:17.380
out of the goodness of his heart.

36:17.381 --> 36:20.116
He needed somebody working there
to man the call girl business.

36:20.117 --> 36:22.619
Not realizing that he was
giving Scarlett full access

36:22.620 --> 36:26.123
- to every facet of his organization.
- Knox didn't steal the client list.

36:26.124 --> 36:28.225
Scarlett gave it to him
so that the two of them

36:28.226 --> 36:29.394
could go into business together.

36:29.395 --> 36:31.495
And when Buckley wouldn't
walk away, Knox killed him,

36:31.595 --> 36:33.464
Never thinking we'd find out
about the call girl ring.

36:33.465 --> 36:34.665
And then when we did,
Scarlett realized

36:34.765 --> 36:36.867
that the only way to save
herself was by giving up Knox

36:36.868 --> 36:39.171
by playing the ultimate victim,
making you believe that Knox

36:39.172 --> 36:41.540
Beat her up so we'd think she
killed him out of self-defense.

36:41.541 --> 36:42.741
And I fell for it.

36:42.941 --> 36:44.209
- We all did.
- I didn't.

36:47.178 --> 36:49.080
Hi. How can I make you happy today?

36:50.081 --> 36:53.583
Yes, Candy is absolutely available.

36:53.584 --> 36:54.619
How would you like her to look?

36:56.920 --> 36:58.521
Girl next door sounds perfect.

36:58.722 --> 37:00.224
Can you confirm your client code?

37:02.325 --> 37:04.195
And your card information
is the same?

37:06.496 --> 37:08.832
Great.
Candy will see you at 7:00.

37:16.573 --> 37:18.942
Hi. How can I make you happy today?

37:18.943 --> 37:20.645
Yes, I'm looking for a girl.

37:21.946 --> 37:23.647
Well, you've certainly come
to the right place.

37:24.348 --> 37:25.549
Can you describe her?

37:25.850 --> 37:28.284
She came to New York
in an ancient blue Beetle,

37:28.285 --> 37:31.087
The floor so rusted, it
literally sagged in the middle.

37:31.988 --> 37:34.023
Castle. How did you get this number?

37:34.024 --> 37:35.827
I have a friend
in the publishing business.

37:37.728 --> 37:40.196
I'm sorry if I disappointed you.

37:40.197 --> 37:42.599
I-I just needed to take
a few more jobs

37:42.600 --> 37:43.534
to set myself up.

37:43.635 --> 37:45.802
You never stop manipulating,
do you, Scarlett?

37:46.403 --> 37:48.038
I should be impressed, really,

37:48.639 --> 37:49.706
How easily you played me,

37:49.707 --> 37:53.343
but all I can think about
is how sad it is...

37:55.444 --> 37:59.148
All that brains and beauty
wasted on a heart gone rotten.

37:59.149 --> 38:01.818
You're so busy building up walls
to keep people out,

38:01.819 --> 38:03.888
you don't even realize that
you're the one trapped inside...

38:04.989 --> 38:06.023
All alone.

38:11.061 --> 38:11.962
Will you stand up, please?

38:19.570 --> 38:20.971
You have the right
to remain silent.

38:21.172 --> 38:23.275
Anything you say can and will
be used against you...

38:25.476 --> 38:26.276
Thanks.

38:26.877 --> 38:27.744
For what?

38:27.945 --> 38:29.314
For not saying I told you so.

38:31.115 --> 38:32.783
Oh, that starts tomorrow.

38:32.784 --> 38:34.851
♪♪

38:38.022 --> 38:41.123
♪♪

38:41.124 --> 38:42.760
♪ every day ♪

38:42.761 --> 38:46.529
Oh!
what was that for?

38:46.530 --> 38:48.064
For being the best Dad ever.

38:48.365 --> 38:50.767
It's true, you know. I have
the novelty mug to prove it.

38:50.768 --> 38:53.303
Mm. Thanks for trusting me,

38:54.004 --> 38:56.906
For not pushing when you knew
I was working something out.

38:57.107 --> 39:00.610
Well... I knew when you
were ready, you would tell me.

39:01.911 --> 39:02.946
So here it is...

39:02.947 --> 39:05.815
♪ ...Just next to me ♪

39:06.216 --> 39:08.451
My school is starting
a foreign exchange program

39:08.452 --> 39:09.653
to France.

39:09.854 --> 39:11.755
- France?
- Yeah.

39:11.756 --> 39:14.091
- You weren't kicked out of school?
- No.

39:15.328 --> 39:16.928
No, the program lasts three weeks,

39:17.028 --> 39:18.996
and so I'd miss your birthday.
And I knew that Beckett

39:18.997 --> 39:20.498
had spent a semester abroad
in college,

39:20.499 --> 39:22.867
and I wanted to ask her if
the experience was worth it.

39:23.668 --> 39:24.568
And what'd she say?

39:24.868 --> 39:27.470
She said that I'd be going off
to college in a couple of years,

39:27.471 --> 39:28.939
and that everything was gonna change,

39:28.940 --> 39:32.743
and maybe it'd be good if we got
a taste of that change now.

39:34.344 --> 39:35.345
Well...

39:36.346 --> 39:37.647
She's a smart woman.

39:37.948 --> 39:39.449
Yeah, she is.

39:40.350 --> 39:43.821
But I decided not to go anyway.

39:45.222 --> 39:47.023
Because two years
will be here soon enough,

39:47.124 --> 39:48.459
And I already got you your present,

39:48.460 --> 39:50.095
and I want to watch you open it.

39:51.096 --> 39:52.096
Mm.

